{{Infobox project
| abbreviation = JSY
| native_name= जननी सुरक्षा योजना
| country = India
| primeminister = Manmohan Singh
| launched = {{Start date and age|2005|4|12|df=y}}
}}
'''Janani Suraksha Yojana''' ('''JSY''') ({{lang-hi|जननी सुरक्षा योजना|translation=Mother Security Scheme}}) is an Indian Government scheme proposed by the [[Government of India]]. It was launched on 12 April 2005 by the [[Prime Minister of India]] on the birth anniversary of [[Kasturba Gandhi]].<ref>[http://www.nrhm.maharashtra.gov.in/schjsy.htm Janani Suraksha Yojana - NRHM | Government of Maharashtra]</ref> It aims to decrease the neo-natal and maternal [[deaths]] happening in the country by promoting [[institutional]] delivery of babies. This is a safe motherhood intervention under the [[National Rural Health Mission]] (NRHM).<ref name="NHRM">{{cite web|title=National Health Mission, Government of India|url=http://nrhm.gov.in/nrhm-components/rmnch-a/maternal-health/janani-suraksha-yojana/background.html|accessdate=11 March 2015}}</ref>

It is a 100% centrally sponsored scheme it integrates cash assistance with delivery and post-delivery care. The success of the scheme would 
be determined by the increase in institutional delivery among the poor families.<ref>[http://ayushmanbharat.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/JSR.pdf Janani Suraksha Yojana| Features & Frequently Asked Questions & Answers]</ref>

