 Fullam]] | driver |rowspan=2| 1985 |rowspan=2| APBA |rowspan=2| |rowspan=2| [[Key West]] |rowspan=2| Still Crazy |rowspan=2| Fullam had a previous career as a CFL player<ref name="siMAG1120213">[https://archive.is/20120719025858/http://vault.sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1120213/index.htm ]</ref> |- | Mike Poppa | Throttleman |- | Mark Lavin | Throttleman | 1986 | APBA | | [[Marathon Fl., Seven Mile Bridge]] | Jesse James |<ref name="historyofoffshore"/> |- | [[Didier Pironi]] | Driver |rowspan=3| 1987/08/23 |rowspan=3| Offshore World Championship |rowspan=3| Needles Trophy |rowspan=3| [[Isle of Wight]], United Kingdom |rowspan=3| ACX "Colibri" - [[Lamborghini]] |rowspan=3| <ref>{{cite web|author=The Motorsport Memorial Team, info@motorsportmemorial.org |url=http://www.motorsportmemorial.org/focus.php?db=b&n=3417 |title=Motorsport Memorial |publisher=Motorsport Memorial |date= |accessdate=2014-07-23}}</ref> Pironi was previously a [[Formula One]] racing driver for [[Ferrari]]. He retired from racing cars due to injuries sustained in an accident at the [[1982 German Grand Prix]]. |- | Jean-Claude Guénard | Throttleman |- | Bernard Giroux | Navigator |- | Thomas Brandt |pilot |rowspan=2| 1988 |rowspan=2| APBA |rowspan=2| Sheffield Oil Unocal 76 Offshore Classic |rowspan=2| [[Panama City, Florida]] |rowspan=2| Spirit of Miss Liberty |rowspan=2| <ref name="washpost1P2-1251501">{{cite journal|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-1251501.html|title=POWERBOATING|date=17 April 1988|publisher=|accessdate=30 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.offshoreonly.com/forums/classic-offshore/195167-c-5-finish-line-3.html |title=C-5 Finish Line - Page 3 |publisher=Offshoreonly.com |date=2008-09-13 |accessdate=2014-07-23}}</ref> |- | Don Wright | throttleman |- | Kevin Brown | Owner/Driver | 1989/10/23 | APBA/UIM Worlds Championship | Atlantic City, New Jersey | 32&nbsp;ft Skater | Team Skater UIM II (Modified Class)Jim Dyke throttle-Man Kevin Brow