{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Mattha Smith | fullname = Matthew Smith<ref name="Benson"/> | birth_date = 31 December 1897 | birth_place = [[Stevenston]], Scotland | death_date = {{death date and age |1953|5|16|1897|12|31|df=yes}}<ref name="Benson"/> | death_place = [[Kilmarnock]], Scotland<ref name="Litster" /> | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | years1 = {{0|0000}}–1916 | clubs1 = [[Ardeer Thistle F.C.|Ardeer Thistle]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 1916–1931 | clubs2 = [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]] | caps2 = 349 | goals2 = 85 | years3 = 1931–1933 | clubs3 = [[Ayr United F.C.|Ayr United]] | caps3 = 33 | goals3 = 3 | years4 = 1933–1934 | clubs4 = [[Galston F.C.|Galston]] | caps4 = | goals4 = }}
'''Matthew''' '''Smith''' (31 December 1897 – 16 May 1953) was a Scottish professional [[Association football|football]] [[Forward (association football)|forward]] who made over 340 appearances in the [[Scottish Football League|Scottish League]] for [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]] and was [[Captain (association football)|captain]] of the club.<ref name="Fitbastats">{{Cite web |url=http://www.fitbastats.com/kilmarnock/player.php?playerid=7115 |title=Kilmarnock Player Mattha Smith Details |website=www.fitbastats.com |access-date=2 August 2016}}</ref> After retiring from football, he [[Coach (association football)|coached]] at [[Ardrossan Winton Rovers F.C.|Ardrossan Winton Rovers]] and returned to Kilmarnock as a [[Scout (association football)|scout]].<ref name="HOF">{{Cite web |url=http://www.kilmarnockfc.co.uk/Article?id=691 |title=Inaugural Kilmarnock FC Hall Of Fame Dinner |website=www.kilmarnockfc.co.uk |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816155139/http://www.kilmarnockfc.co.uk/Article?id=691 |archive-date=16 August 2016 |dead-url=yes |access-date=2 August 2016}}</ref><ref name="Benson">{{Cite web|url=http://www.killiefc.com/en/mattha-smith_49804/|title=Mattha Smith {{!}} Former Players|website=www.killiefc.com|access-date=2 August 2016}}</ref>
