{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Use British English|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox cricketer | name = | country = England | fullname = William Batson | nickname = | heightft = | heightinch = | heightm = | batting = Right-handed | bowling = | role = | family = | club1 = [[Northamptonshire County Cricket Club|Northamptonshire]] | year1 = 1920–1921 | clubnumber1 = | deliveries = balls | columns = 1 | column1 = [[First-class cricket|First-class]] | matches1 = 2 | runs1 = 45 | bat avg1 = 11.25 | 100s/50s1 = –/– | top score1 = 34 | deliveries1 = – | wickets1 = – | bowl avg1 = – | fivefor1 = – | tenfor1 = – | best bowling1 = – | catches/stumpings1 = –/– | date = 17 November | year = 2011 | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/9607.html Cricinfo }}
'''William Batson''' (dates of birth and death unknown) was an English [[cricket]]er. Batson was a right-handed [[Batting (cricket)|batsman]].
Batson made two [[first-class cricket|first-class]] appearances for [[Northamptonshire County Cricket Club|Northamptonshire]] against [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]] in the [[1920 County Championship]] and [[Warwickshire County Cricket Club|Warwickshire]] in the [[1921 County Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/27/27756/First-Class_Matches.html|title=First-Class Matches played by William Batson|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=17 November 2011}}</ref> In the match against Surrey at [[The Oval]], he scored 9 runs in Northamptonshire's first-innings, before being dismissed by [[Percy Fender]], while in their second-innings he was dismissed for a [[duck (cricket)|duck]] by the same bowler.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/9/9750.html|title=Surrey v Northamptonshire, 1920 County Championship|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=17 November 2011}}</ref> Against Warwickshire at the [[County Ground, Northampton|County Ground]], he scored 2 runs before being dismissed by [[Gerard Rotherham]], while in their second-innings he was dismissed by [[Harry Howell (cricketer)|Harry Howell]], having scored 14 runs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/10/10077.html|title=Northamptonshire v Warwickshire, 1921 County Championship|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=17 November 2011}}</ref>
